text: Typhoon Forrest known in the Philippines as Typhoon Ising was the most intense Tropical cyclones of the 20th century stands as a significant event in meteorological history. Forming in September 1983 this Typhoon exhibited rapid intensifiation that challenged forecasters and left a lasting impact on the Regions it affected. title: Typhoon Forrest (1983)
